           <h3>About the Author <span class="profile">(<a rel="author" href="http://blogs.kqed.org/bayareabites/?author=566">Author Archive</a>)</span></h3> Shelby Pope is a freelance writer living and eating her way through Oakland. She’s written about food, art and science for publications including The Bold Italic, The East Bay Express and The Toast. When she’s not taste testing sourdough bread to find the Bay Area’s best loaf, you can find her on Twitter @shelbylpope 
