             <div id="dsq-comment-body-166272" class="dsq-comment-body"> 
              <div id="dsq-comment-message-166272" class="dsq-comment-message">
               <p>Great stuff. As with many ‘foodies’, I think more these days about how food is made and the varied food distribution systems, as well as balancing the cost differences between buying chicken that is mass produced vs raised by Aunt Sally and her Kids at local farm X and costs 2-3x as much. I respect the effort and how it is changing our perceptions about food and quality, but often…even if hormone free and free range, pastured chickens are healthier, am I willing to pay the price per pound?</p> 
               <p>Sometimes.</p> 
