          <div class="post"> 
           <div class="entry clearfix"> 
            <a href="http://blogs.kqed.org/bayareabites/2015/02/03/bay-area-bites-guide-to-10-favorite-raw-oyster-spots-in-the-east-bay/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Bay Area Bites Guide to 10 Favorite Raw Oyster Spots in the East Bay"> <img class="thumbnail" src="http://blogs.kqed.org/bayareabites/files/2015/01/Hopscotch_oysters1000-288x162.jpg" alt="Bay Area Bites Guide to 10 Favorite Raw Oyster Spots in the East Bay" title="Bay Area Bites Guide to 10 Favorite Raw Oyster Spots in the East Bay"> </a> 
            <p class="post-title"><a href="http://blogs.kqed.org/bayareabites/2015/02/03/bay-area-bites-guide-to-10-favorite-raw-oyster-spots-in-the-east-bay/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Bay Area Bites Guide to 10 Favorite Raw Oyster Spots in the East Bay">Bay Area Bites Guide to 10 Favorite Raw Oyster Spots in the East Bay</a></p> 
            <p>Few people have a middling relationship to raw oysters—this mysterious, ubiquitous bivalve is loved and loathed in equal measure. These ten East Bay spots fall on the love end of the spectrum, and offer the best quality and presentation of these strange and healthful sea creatures on the east side of the bay. </p> 
           </div> 
           <div class="meta single"> 
            <span class="meta-author"> <a href="http://blogs.kqed.org/bayareabites/author/kimwesterman/" title="Posts by Kim Westerman" rel="author">Kim Westerman</a> | </span> 
            <span class="meta-date"> February 3, 2015 </span> 
            <span class="meta-comments"> | <a href="http://blogs.kqed.org/bayareabites/2015/02/03/bay-area-bites-guide-to-10-favorite-raw-oyster-spots-in-the-east-bay/#comments" rel="bookmark" title="Comments for Bay Area Bites Guide to 10 Favorite Raw Oyster Spots in the East Bay"><span class="dsq-postid" rel="92680 http://blogs.kqed.org/bayareabites/?p=92680">2 Comments</span></a> </span> 
           </div> 
           <div style="clear:both;"></div> 
          </div> 
          <div class="post"> 
           <div class="entry clearfix"> 
            <a href="http://blogs.kqed.org/bayareabites/2015/02/02/bay-area-bites-guide-to-10-popular-south-bay-banh-mi-shops/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Bay Area Bites Guide to 10 Popular South Bay Bánh Mì Shops"> <img class="thumbnail" src="http://blogs.kqed.org/bayareabites/files/2015/01/KimsCharcoal-288x162.jpg" alt="Bay Area Bites Guide to 10 Popular South Bay Bánh Mì Shops" title="Bay Area Bites Guide to 10 Popular South Bay Bánh Mì Shops"> </a> 
            <p class="post-title"><a href="http://blogs.kqed.org/bayareabites/2015/02/02/bay-area-bites-guide-to-10-popular-south-bay-banh-mi-shops/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Bay Area Bites Guide to 10 Popular South Bay Bánh Mì Shops">Bay Area Bites Guide to 10 Popular South Bay Bánh Mì Shops</a></p> 
            <p>It is easy to see why bánh mì are so popular. A leftover influence from French colonization, these Vietnamese sandwiches are inexpensive and bursting with great flavors and textures. Here is a list of ten unique bánh mì shops in the South Bay. </p> 
           </div> 
           <div class="meta single"> 
            <span class="meta-author"> <a href="http://blogs.kqed.org/bayareabites/author/jeffcianci/" title="Posts by Jeff Cianci" rel="author">Jeff Cianci</a> | </span> 
            <span class="meta-date"> February 2, 2015 </span> 
            <span class="meta-comments"> | <a href="http://blogs.kqed.org/bayareabites/2015/02/02/bay-area-bites-guide-to-10-popular-south-bay-banh-mi-shops/#comments" rel="bookmark" title="Comments for Bay Area Bites Guide to 10 Popular South Bay Bánh Mì Shops"><span class="dsq-postid" rel="92575 http://blogs.kqed.org/bayareabites/?p=92575">10 Comments</span></a> </span> 
           </div> 
           <div style="clear:both;"></div> 
